{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FkPxEiKJNVtaa84hqMXMwD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     5→import lombok.AccessLevel;\n     6→import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Data;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n    10→\n    11→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    12→import java.util.UUID;\n    13→\n    14→@Data\n    15→@AllArgsConstructor(access = AccessLevel.PROTECTED)\n    16→public class Comment {\n    17→  @NotNull private final UUID id;\n    18→  @NotNull private final User author;\n    19→  @NotNull private final Article article;\n    20→  @NotBlank private final String body;\n    21→  @NotNull private final LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    22→  private final LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019295cPrXCELDJndVHtddDp","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"40924695-97f5-40c3-8da1-eb4d9d597d65"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N5u49BBhL5kWdMVo8pMUz4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.User;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.validator.ModelValidator;\n     8→\n     9→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class CommentBuilder {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ModelValidator modelValidator;\n    17→\n    18→    public Comment build(User author, Article article, String body) {\n    19→        final var createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();\n    20→        return modelValidator.validate(\n    21→                new Comment(UUID.randomUUID(), author, article, body, createdAt, createdAt));\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public Comment build(\n    25→            UUID id,\n    26→            User author,\n    27→            Article article,\n    28→            String body,\n    29→            LocalDateTime createdAt,\n    30→            LocalDateTime updatedAt) {\n    31→        return modelValidator.validate(new Comment(id, author, article, body, createdAt, updatedAt));\n    32→    }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019295cPrXCELDJndVHtddDp","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"663de8a1-1d74-40f5-adf9-c2275e037cb2"}
