{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XujSyLuZdkTSESP2JhtPuV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Query;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.repository.entity.*;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    12→\n    13→public abstract class AbstractDAO<ENTITY, ID> {\n    14→\n    15→    @PersistenceContext\n    16→    protected EntityManager em;\n    17→\n    18→    protected UserEntity findUserEntityById(UUID id) {\n    19→        return em.find(UserEntity.class, id);\n    20→    }\n    21→\n    22→    protected TagEntity findTagEntityById(UUID id) {\n    23→        return em.find(TagEntity.class, id);\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    protected ArticleEntity findArticleEntityById(UUID id) {\n    27→        return em.find(ArticleEntity.class, id);\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    protected CommentEntity findCommentEntityById(UUID id) {\n    31→        return em.find(CommentEntity.class, id);\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    protected FavoriteRelationshipEntity findFavoriteRelationshipEntityByKey(\n    35→            FavoriteRelationship favoriteRelationship) {\n    36→\n    37→        Query query = em.createNamedQuery(\"FVREfindByArticleAndUserID\");\n    38→        query.setParameter(\"articleId\", favoriteRelationship.getArticle().getId());\n    39→        query.setParameter(\"currentUserId\", favoriteRelationship.getUser().getId());\n    40→\n    41→        List<FavoriteRelationshipEntity> resultList = query.getResultList();\n    42→        if (!resultList.isEmpty()) {\n    43→            return (resultList.get(0));\n    44→        } else {\n    45→            return null;\n    46→        }\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    protected boolean isNotEmpty(List<?> list) {\n    50→        return list != null && !list.isEmpty();\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    protected List<String> toUpperCase(List<String> subjectList) {\n    54→        return subjectList.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    55→    }\n    56→}\n    57→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"646515ae-8d92-4cc5-919f-e0c743508a59"}
