{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011ndnuZf8GU52Gp6MRw3f9L","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolationException;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\n    11→\n    12→@Provider\n    13→public class BeanValidationExceptionMapper\n    14→        implements ExceptionMapper<ConstraintViolationException> {\n    15→\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public Response toResponse(ConstraintViolationException e) {\n    21→\n    22→        ErrorResponse errorResponse = new ErrorResponse();\n    23→\n    24→        e.getConstraintViolations()\n    25→                .iterator()\n    26→                .forEachRemaining(\n    27→                        contraint -> {\n    28→                            errorResponse.getBody().add(contraint.getMessage());\n    29→                        });\n    30→\n    31→        try {\n    32→            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse)).status(422).build();\n    33→        } catch (JsonProcessingException ex) {\n    34→            throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    35→        }\n    36→    }\n    37→}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"d3f746a6-e9d9-40ad-a25a-52cceba3a1e4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EVV2P2iJNahWeV25go4vuj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.exceptions.JWTVerificationException;\n     4→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ResourceInfo;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.HttpHeaders;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    15→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.UnauthorizedException;\n    16→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n    17→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    18→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context.DecodedJWTSecurityContext;\n    19→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context.EmptySecurityContext;\n    20→\n    21→import java.io.IOException;\n    22→import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n    23→\n    24→@Secured\n    25→@Provider\n    26→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHENTICATION)\n    27→public class AuthenticationFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    28→\n    29→    private final String AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX = \"Token \";\n    30→\n    31→    @Inject\n    32→    TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    33→\n    34→    @Context\n    35→    private ResourceInfo resourceInfo;\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext containerRequestContext) throws IOException {\n    39→\n    40→        String authorizationHeader = containerRequestContext.getHeaderString(HttpHeaders.AUTHORIZATION);\n    41→\n    42→        if (authorizationHeader != null\n    43→                && authorizationHeader.startsWith(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX)) {\n    44→\n    45→            String token = authorizationHeader.replace(AUTHORIZATION_HEADER_PREFIX, \"\");\n    46→\n    47→            try {\n    48→\n    49→                DecodedJWT decodedJWT = tokenProvider.verify(token);\n    50→\n    51→                containerRequestContext.setSecurityContext(\n    52→                        new DecodedJWTSecurityContext(decodedJWT, tokenProvider));\n    53→\n    54→            } catch (JWTVerificationException ex) {\n    55→                containerRequestContext.abortWith(\n    56→                        Response.ok(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.toString())\n    57→                                .status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED)\n    58→                                .build());\n    59→            }\n    60→        } else {\n    61→\n    62→            containerRequestContext.setSecurityContext(new EmptySecurityContext());\n    63→\n    64→            if (!isSecurityOptional()) {\n    65→                throw new UnauthorizedException();\n    66→            }\n    67→        }\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    private boolean isSecurityOptional() {\n    71→\n    72→        Class<?> resourceClass = resourceInfo.getResourceClass();\n    73→        Method resourceMethod = resourceInfo.getResourceMethod();\n    74→        Secured resourceClassSecured = resourceClass.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    75→        Secured resourceMethodSecured = resourceMethod.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    76→\n    77→        if (resourceMethodSecured != null) {\n    78→            return resourceMethodSecured.optional();\n    79→        }\n    80→\n    81→        if (resourceClassSecured != null) {\n    82→            return resourceClassSecured.optional();\n    83→        }\n    84→\n    85→        return false;\n    86→    }\n    87→}\n    88→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"59653fe2-4540-4d7b-ba52-7e3c94c725a4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WVS1LKgnCScLbnzh3sHHXX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.filter;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.Priority;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.Priorities;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestContext;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ContainerRequestFilter;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.container.ResourceInfo;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.exception.ForbiddenException;\n    13→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation.Secured;\n    14→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n    15→\n    16→import java.io.IOException;\n    17→import java.lang.reflect.AnnotatedElement;\n    18→import java.lang.reflect.Method;\n    19→import java.util.Arrays;\n    20→import java.util.LinkedList;\n    21→import java.util.List;\n    22→\n    23→@Secured\n    24→@Provider\n    25→@Priority(Priorities.AUTHORIZATION)\n    26→public class AuthorizationFilter implements ContainerRequestFilter {\n    27→\n    28→    @Context\n    29→    private ResourceInfo resourceInfo;\n    30→\n    31→    @Override\n    32→    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext containerRequestContext) throws IOException {\n    33→\n    34→        Class<?> resourceClass = resourceInfo.getResourceClass();\n    35→        Method resourceMethod = resourceInfo.getResourceMethod();\n    36→\n    37→        if (!isSecurityOptional(resourceMethod, resourceClass)) {\n    38→            SecurityContext securityContext = containerRequestContext.getSecurityContext();\n    39→\n    40→            List<Role> classRoles = extractRoles(resourceClass);\n    41→            List<Role> methodRoles = extractRoles(resourceMethod);\n    42→\n    43→            try {\n    44→                if (methodRoles.isEmpty()) {\n    45→                    checkPermissions(classRoles, securityContext);\n    46→                } else {\n    47→                    checkPermissions(methodRoles, securityContext);\n    48→                }\n    49→            } catch (Exception ex) {\n    50→                containerRequestContext.abortWith(Response.status(Response.Status.FORBIDDEN).build());\n    51→            }\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    private boolean isSecurityOptional(Method resourceMethod, Class<?> resourceClass) {\n    56→        Secured resourceClassSecured = resourceClass.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    57→        Secured resourceMethodSecured = resourceMethod.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    58→\n    59→        if (resourceMethodSecured != null) {\n    60→            return resourceMethodSecured.optional();\n    61→        }\n    62→\n    63→        if (resourceClassSecured != null) {\n    64→            return resourceClassSecured.optional();\n    65→        }\n    66→\n    67→        return false;\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    private void checkPermissions(List<Role> allowedRoles, SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    71→        if (!isAccessAllowed(allowedRoles, securityContext)) {\n    72→            throw new ForbiddenException();\n    73→        }\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    private boolean isAccessAllowed(List<Role> allowedRoles, SecurityContext securityContext) {\n    77→        for (Role allowedRole : allowedRoles) {\n    78→            if (securityContext.isUserInRole(allowedRole.name())) {\n    79→                return true;\n    80→            }\n    81→        }\n    82→        return false;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    private List<Role> extractRoles(AnnotatedElement annotatedElement) {\n    86→        if (annotatedElement == null) {\n    87→            return new LinkedList<>();\n    88→        } else {\n    89→            Secured secured = annotatedElement.getAnnotation(Secured.class);\n    90→            if (secured == null) {\n    91→                return new LinkedList<>();\n    92→            } else {\n    93→                return Arrays.asList(secured.value());\n    94→            }\n    95→        }\n    96→    }\n    97→}\n    98→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"71509992-ba30-434a-9445-39ad5275fbd7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FBPTyc7vZAAYfdC3fGZqbT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context;\n     2→\n     3→import com.auth0.jwt.interfaces.DecodedJWT;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.provider.TokenProvider;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n     7→\n     8→import java.security.Principal;\n     9→\n    10→public class DecodedJWTSecurityContext implements SecurityContext {\n    11→\n    12→    private final DecodedJWT decodedJWT;\n    13→    private final TokenProvider tokenProvider;\n    14→\n    15→    public DecodedJWTSecurityContext(DecodedJWT decodedJWT, TokenProvider tokenProvider) {\n    16→        this.decodedJWT = decodedJWT;\n    17→        this.tokenProvider = tokenProvider;\n    18→    }\n    19→\n    20→    @Override\n    21→    public Principal getUserPrincipal() {\n    22→        return decodedJWT::getSubject;\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    @Override\n    26→    public boolean isUserInRole(String role) {\n    27→        Role[] tokenRoles = tokenProvider.extractRoles(decodedJWT);\n    28→        for (Role tokenRole : tokenRoles) {\n    29→            if (role.equals(tokenRole.name())) {\n    30→                return true;\n    31→            }\n    32→        }\n    33→        return false;\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    @Override\n    37→    public boolean isSecure() {\n    38→        return false;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    @Override\n    42→    public String getAuthenticationScheme() {\n    43→        return null;\n    44→    }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"51885d61-14af-42c3-a779-7fcc3dfb306f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0165sLGecjzxHT8h3aNGGGrZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.context;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.SecurityContext;\n     4→\n     5→import java.security.Principal;\n     6→\n     7→public class EmptySecurityContext implements SecurityContext {\n     8→    @Override\n     9→    public Principal getUserPrincipal() {\n    10→        return null;\n    11→    }\n    12→\n    13→    @Override\n    14→    public boolean isUserInRole(String s) {\n    15→        return false;\n    16→    }\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public boolean isSecure() {\n    20→        return false;\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public String getAuthenticationScheme() {\n    25→        return null;\n    26→    }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"274f51f7-24d6-4fc9-90e8-099fa3888013"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BSEYat8rHaHeerP8wJU451","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.validator;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintValidator;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintValidatorContext;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull;\n     6→\n     7→import java.lang.reflect.Field;\n     8→\n     9→public class AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator implements ConstraintValidator<AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull, Object> {\n    10→\n    11→    private String[] fieldNames;\n    12→\n    13→    public void initialize(AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull constraintAnnotation) {\n    14→        fieldNames = constraintAnnotation.fieldNames();\n    15→    }\n    16→\n    17→    public boolean isValid(Object object, ConstraintValidatorContext constraintValidatorContext) {\n    18→\n    19→        Class<?> clazz = object.getClass();\n    20→\n    21→        configFieldNamesIfEmpty(clazz);\n    22→\n    23→        for (String propertyName : fieldNames) {\n    24→            Field field = getDeclaredField(clazz, propertyName);\n    25→            if (getValue(field, object) != null) {\n    26→                return true;\n    27→            }\n    28→        }\n    29→\n    30→        return false;\n    31→    }\n    32→\n    33→    private void configFieldNamesIfEmpty(Class<?> clazz) {\n    34→\n    35→        if (fieldNames.length == 0) {\n    36→            fieldNames = getInstanceDeclaredFieldNames(clazz);\n    37→        }\n    38→\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    private String[] getInstanceDeclaredFieldNames(Class<?> clazz) {\n    42→\n    43→        Field[] fields = clazz.getDeclaredFields();\n    44→\n    45→        String[] resultNames = new String[fields.length];\n    46→\n    47→        for (int fieldIndex = 0; fieldIndex < fields.length; fieldIndex++) {\n    48→            resultNames[fieldIndex] = fields[fieldIndex].getName();\n    49→        }\n    50→\n    51→        return resultNames;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    private Object getValue(Field field, Object instance) {\n    55→        Object value;\n    56→        try {\n    57→            value = field.get(instance);\n    58→        } catch (IllegalAccessException ex) {\n    59→            throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    60→        }\n    61→        return value;\n    62→    }\n    63→\n    64→    private Field getDeclaredField(Class<?> clazz, String name) {\n    65→        Field field;\n    66→        try {\n    67→            field = clazz.getDeclaredField(name);\n    68→            field.setAccessible(true);\n    69→        } catch (NoSuchFieldException ex) {\n    70→            throw new RuntimeException(ex);\n    71→        }\n    72→        return field;\n    73→    }\n    74→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"14c59114-0204-49db-99c2-85a33857a9c5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01W6dcmUgjs1hGRVunqbQixJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.constraint;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.Constraint;\n     4→import jakarta.validation.Payload;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.validation.validator.AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator;\n     6→\n     7→import java.lang.annotation.*;\n     8→\n     9→@Target({ElementType.TYPE})\n    10→@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n    11→@Constraint(validatedBy = AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNullValidator.class)\n    12→@Documented\n    13→public @interface AtLeastOneFieldMustBeNotNull {\n    14→\n    15→    String message() default \"At least one field must be not null\";\n    16→\n    17→    Class<?>[] groups() default {};\n    18→\n    19→    Class<? extends Payload>[] payload() default {};\n    20→\n    21→    String[] fieldNames() default {};\n    22→\n    23→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"88df0e3f-e393-4626-84cf-91d80122254d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TDPAf8kHz9ywEpu3dwvpeD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the requested files. Let me create a comprehensive summary with all the file contents:\n\n## Complete File Contents Report\n\nBelow are the full contents of all requested files from the project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. SecurityFilter.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n---\n\n### 2. ObjectMapperProvider.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n---\n\n### 3. CorsFilter.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n---\n\n### 4. BusinessExceptionMapper.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/mapper/BusinessExceptionMapper.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.mapper;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\nimport jakarta.inject.Inject;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ExceptionMapper;\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.ext.Provider;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response.ErrorResponse;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.*;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.function.Function;\n\n@Provider\npublic class BusinessExceptionMapper implements ExceptionMapper<BusinessException> {\n\n    @Inject\n    ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n\n    private final Map<Class<? extends BusinessException>, Function<BusinessException, Response>>\n            exceptionMapper;\n\n    public BusinessExceptionMapper() {\n        this.exceptionMapper = configureExceptionMapper();\n    }\n\n    private Map<Class<? extends BusinessException>, Function<BusinessException, Response>>\n    configureExceptionMapper() {\n\n        final var handlerMap =\n                new HashMap<Class<? extends BusinessException>, Function<BusinessException, Response>>();\n\n        handlerMap.put(EmailAlreadyExistsException.class, this::conflict);\n        handlerMap.put(UserNotFoundException.class, this::notFound);\n        handlerMap.put(InvalidPasswordException.class, this::unauthorized);\n        handlerMap.put(UsernameAlreadyExistsException.class, this::conflict);\n        handlerMap.put(TagNotFoundException.class, this::notFound);\n        handlerMap.put(ArticleNotFoundException.class, this::notFound);\n        handlerMap.put(ModelValidationException.class, this::unprocessableEntity);\n\n        return handlerMap;\n    }\n\n    private Response notFound(BusinessException businessException) {\n        try {\n            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse(businessException)))\n                    .status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND.getStatusCode())\n                    .build();\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private Response conflict(BusinessException businessException) {\n        try {\n            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse(businessException)))\n                    .status(Response.Status.CONFLICT.getStatusCode())\n                    .build();\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private Response unauthorized(BusinessException businessException) {\n        try {\n            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse(businessException)))\n                    .status(Response.Status.UNAUTHORIZED.getStatusCode())\n                    .build();\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private Response unprocessableEntity(BusinessException businessException) {\n        try {\n            return Response.ok(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(errorResponse(businessException))).status(422).build();\n        } catch (JsonProcessingException e) {\n            throw new RuntimeException(e);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private ErrorResponse errorResponse(BusinessException businessException) {\n        return new ErrorResponse(businessException.getMessages());\n    }\n\n    @Override\n    public Response toResponse(BusinessException businessException) {\n        return this.exceptionMapper.get(businessException.getClass()).apply(businessException);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. CatchAllExceptionMapper.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n---\n\n### 6. ConstraintViolationExceptionMapper.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n**Note:** A similar file exists: `BeanValidationExceptionMapper.java`\n\n---\n\n### 7. ModelValidationExceptionMapper.java\n**Status:** File does not exist at the specified path\n\n---\n\n### 8. Secured.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/example/realworldapi/infrastructure/web/security/annotation/Secured.java`\n\n```java\npackage org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.annotation;\n\nimport jakarta.ws.rs.NameBinding;\nimport org.example.realworldapi.infrastructure.web.security.profile.Role;\n\nimport java.lang.annotation.ElementType;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Retention;\nimport java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;\nimport java.lang.annotation.Target;\n\n@NameBinding\n@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)\n@Target({ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD})\npublic @interface Secured {\n    Role[] value() default {};\n\n    boolean optional() default false;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. Role.java\n**Path:** `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/s