{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AtTTThQykcSiwDbZFW17yk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteComment;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.DeleteCommentInput;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class DeleteCommentImpl implements DeleteComment {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FindCommentByIdAndAuthor findCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public void handle(DeleteCommentInput deleteCommentInput) {\n    20→        final var comment =\n    21→                findCommentByIdAndAuthor.handle(\n    22→                        deleteCommentInput.getCommentId(), deleteCommentInput.getAuthorId());\n    23→        commentRepository.delete(comment);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"267a3a58-aeca-4263-abf8-ea3525b1ec84"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Tj4Ai8tU9j37v9AApXodHX","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.DeleteArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationship;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    10→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n    11→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n    12→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→import java.util.Optional;\n    16→import java.util.UUID;\n    17→\n    18→@Singleton\n    19→public class DeleteArticleBySlugImpl implements DeleteArticleBySlug {\n    20→\n    21→    @Inject\n    22→    private FindArticleByAuthorAndSlug findArticleByAuthorAndSlug;\n    23→    @Inject\n    24→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    31→\n    32→    @Override\n    33→    public void handle(UUID authorId, String slug) {\n    34→        final var article = findArticleByAuthorAndSlug.handle(authorId, slug);\n    35→        tagRelationshipRepository.delete(article);\n    36→        Optional<FavoriteRelationship> favorite = favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), authorId);\n    37→        favorite.ifPresent(favoriteRelationship -> favoriteRelationshipRepository.delete(favoriteRelationship));\n    38→        List<Comment> comments = commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    39→        comments.forEach(c -> commentRepository.delete(c));\n    40→        articleRepository.delete(article);\n    41→    }\n    42→}\n    43→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"89ac726f-24ea-4b4c-9b45-17d8b5f19959"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UztvgTYEaeswqDSGwBB2U9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateTag;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagBuilder;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     9→\n    10→@Singleton\n    11→public class CreateTagImpl implements CreateTag {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private TagBuilder tagBuilder;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Tag handle(String name) {\n    20→        final var tag = tagBuilder.build(name);\n    21→        tagRepository.save(tag);\n    22→        return tag;\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"de839bfa-7571-418d-93f3-840e5a8886f3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WhQG49UQLG6vsdhdBWg7gq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.CreateSlugByTitle;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.provider.SlugProvider;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class CreateSlugByTitleImpl implements CreateSlugByTitle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private SlugProvider slugProvider;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public String handle(String title) {\n    21→        String slug = slugProvider.slugify(title);\n    22→        if (articleRepository.existsBySlug(slug)) {\n    23→            slug += UUID.randomUUID().toString();\n    24→        }\n    25→        return slug;\n    26→    }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"2bcf73b6-13c6-40ab-ac03-fedfc3f8c593"}
