{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014HpStEt9Q67RcPFnjyEm17","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.IsFollowingUser;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.user.FollowRelationshipRepository;\n     7→\n     8→import java.util.UUID;\n     9→\n    10→@Dependent\n    11→public class IsFollowingUserImpl implements IsFollowingUser {\n    12→\n    13→    @Inject\n    14→    private FollowRelationshipRepository usersFollowedRepository;\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public boolean handle(UUID currentUserId, UUID followedUserId) {\n    18→        return usersFollowedRepository.isFollowing(currentUserId, followedUserId);\n    19→    }\n    20→}\n    21→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"27060ab8-d54c-43c6-9ab4-bc069034f168"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Y84BnrfAGHWAWPt9qwEzCT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.UnfavoriteArticle;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.FavoriteRelationshipRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.UUID;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class UnfavoriteArticleImpl implements UnfavoriteArticle {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    16→    @Inject\n    17→    private FavoriteRelationshipRepository favoriteRelationshipRepository;\n    18→\n    19→    @Override\n    20→    public void handle(String articleSlug, UUID currentUserId) {\n    21→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(articleSlug);\n    22→        final var favoriteRelationshipOptional =\n    23→                favoriteRelationshipRepository.findByArticleIdAndUserId(article.getId(), currentUserId);\n    24→        favoriteRelationshipOptional.ifPresent(favoriteRelationshipRepository::delete);\n    25→    }\n    26→}\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"b8114a30-1bba-4bbb-96d6-09e729f6effd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BKbCe4RSpMSydXQbauwMPW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleBySlug;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentsByArticleSlug;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindCommentsByArticleSlugImpl implements FindCommentsByArticleSlug {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private FindArticleBySlug findArticleBySlug;\n    17→    @Inject\n    18→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    19→\n    20→    @Override\n    21→    public List<Comment> handle(String slug) {\n    22→        final var article = findArticleBySlug.handle(slug);\n    23→        return commentRepository.findCommentsByArticle(article);\n    24→    }\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"57a07970-418e-4dab-9d44-274aca0bca0f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QP5ok8jQqVYun7jZWtpjfe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.CommentNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindCommentByIdAndAuthor;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.Comment;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.comment.CommentRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindCommentByIdAndAuthorImpl implements FindCommentByIdAndAuthor {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private CommentRepository commentRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Comment handle(UUID commentId, UUID authorId) {\n    20→        return commentRepository\n    21→                .findByIdAndAuthor(commentId, authorId)\n    22→                .orElseThrow(CommentNotFoundException::new);\n    23→    }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"2e530454-a849-472e-a7e8-bc273f1493ee"}
