{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019zULEJBVmwL5nwMHv2RT86","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.TagRepository;\n     8→\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindTagsImpl implements FindTags {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private TagRepository tagRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public List<Tag> handle() {\n    19→        return tagRepository.findAllTags();\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"be3d1fc2-337e-4446-80d1-94b98f8594f0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01A5fHBvVbt4xkKf9b9edvRq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticlesByFilter;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleFilter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.PageResult;\n    10→\n    11→@Singleton\n    12→public class FindArticlesByFilterImpl implements FindArticlesByFilter {\n    13→\n    14→    @Inject\n    15→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    16→\n    17→    @Override\n    18→    public PageResult<Article> handle(ArticleFilter articleFilter) {\n    19→        return articleRepository.findArticlesByFilter(articleFilter);\n    20→    }\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"91152f98-7725-4743-ab18-e620671a8c67"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SUajXyMY1d62BNA7UUhdBa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleTags;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.TagRelationshipRepository;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleTagsImpl implements FindArticleTags {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private TagRelationshipRepository tagRelationshipRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public List<Tag> handle(Article article) {\n    20→        return tagRelationshipRepository.findArticleTags(article);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"028f0903-f93c-48ba-a53c-4ae13550eff5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VJtYzwrYD3siuTGBPJDEiw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.impl;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Singleton;\n     5→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.exception.ArticleNotFoundException;\n     6→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.feature.FindArticleById;\n     7→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.ArticleRepository;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.UUID;\n    11→\n    12→@Singleton\n    13→public class FindArticleByIdImpl implements FindArticleById {\n    14→\n    15→    @Inject\n    16→    private ArticleRepository articleRepository;\n    17→\n    18→    @Override\n    19→    public Article handle(UUID id) {\n    20→        return articleRepository.findArticleById(id).orElseThrow(ArticleNotFoundException::new);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012AGQbfMpSF8tyKV9Zw5HuZ","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"3a3995ad-4b42-43c2-9a0f-79b962f60da0"}
