{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01EQqnCLUMUs6rHeonwsKMRF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see - the wrappers already have the structure `{\"user\": {...}}` as a field called `user`. So the JSON format is `{\"user\": {\"username\":..., \"email\":..., \"password\":...}}`. The wrappers themselves don't use `@JsonRootName` - they just have a `user` field. So when the smoke test sends `{\"user\": {...}}`, the Quarkus Jackson deserializer should be able to handle this.\n\nThe issue is that the old app was using JSON-B and the wrapping ObjectMapper with `UNWRAP_ROOT_VALUE` for deserialization. But with Quarkus REST (RESTEasy Reactive) using Jackson, the deserialization should work since the wrapper classes already match the JSON structure.\n\nLet me check what's actually happening - the 400 error might be from something else. Let me look at the container logs more carefully:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1753,"cache_read_input_tokens":149234,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1753,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":293},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"09a14c22-0b8a-4658-bbaa-f90d90cb23ee"}
