{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01WC6j8CekYJ3oupyagsERAf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.example.realworldapi.application.web.model.response;\n     2→\n     3→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonFormat;\n     4→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonRootName;\n     5→import lombok.Getter;\n     6→import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;\n     7→import lombok.Setter;\n     8→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.article.Article;\n     9→import org.example.realworldapi.domain.model.tag.Tag;\n    10→\n    11→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n    12→import java.util.List;\n    13→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n    14→\n    15→@Getter\n    16→@Setter\n    17→@NoArgsConstructor\n    18→@JsonRootName(\"article\")\n    19→public class ArticleResponse {\n    20→\n    21→    private String slug;\n    22→    private String title;\n    23→    private String description;\n    24→    private String body;\n    25→    private List<String> tagList;\n    26→\n    27→    @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    28→    private LocalDateTime createdAt;\n    29→\n    30→    @JsonFormat(shape = JsonFormat.Shape.STRING, pattern = \"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z'\")\n    31→    private LocalDateTime updatedAt;\n    32→\n    33→    private boolean favorited;\n    34→    private long favoritesCount;\n    35→    private ProfileResponse author;\n    36→\n    37→    public ArticleResponse(\n    38→            Article article, ProfileResponse author, long favoritesCount, List<Tag> tags) {\n    39→        this.slug = article.getSlug();\n    40→        this.title = article.getTitle();\n    41→        this.description = article.getDescription();\n    42→        this.body = article.getBody();\n    43→        this.createdAt = article.getCreatedAt();\n    44→        this.updatedAt = article.getUpdatedAt();\n    45→        this.author = author;\n    46→        this.favoritesCount = favoritesCount;\n    47→        this.tagList = tags.stream().map(Tag::getName).collect(Collectors.toList());\n    48→    }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S77sWo4frnNBhzyJafBjFw","session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"66df08a0-cfce-4143-9453-ea85bae09e2d"}
