{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cy9SgamFYJ633JjK9DkZR3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Quarkus configuration for RealWorld API\n     2→\n     3→# HTTP\n     4→quarkus.http.port=8080\n     5→\n     6→# Datasource configuration\n     7→quarkus.datasource.db-kind=postgresql\n     8→quarkus.datasource.username=${POSTGRESQL_USER:postgres_user}\n     9→quarkus.datasource.password=${POSTGRESQL_PW:S3cret}\n    10→quarkus.datasource.jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://${POSTGRESQL_HOSTNAME:localhost}:${POSTGRESQL_PORT:5432}/${POSTGRESQL_DBNAME:postgres_db}\n    11→\n    12→# Hibernate ORM\n    13→quarkus.hibernate-orm.database.generation=drop-and-create\n    14→quarkus.hibernate-orm.log.sql=false\n    15→\n    16→# JWT custom config\n    17→jwt.issuer=users-service\n    18→jwt.expiration.time.minutes=10\n    19→jwt.secret=secret123\n    20→\n    21→# CORS\n    22→quarkus.http.cors=true\n    23→quarkus.http.cors.origins=*\n    24→quarkus.http.cors.methods=GET,POST,PUT,DELETE,OPTIONS\n    25→quarkus.http.cors.headers=*\n    26→quarkus.http.cors.access-control-allow-credentials=true\n    27→quarkus.http.cors.access-control-max-age=3600\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"fca2c187-04c9-4515-b5a2-7b941abdf0f3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GezoBbKRZ6LxtK6BDyafP8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→\n     6→    <groupId>projects</groupId>\n     7→    <artifactId>realworld-quarkus</artifactId>\n     8→    <version>1.0.0</version>\n     9→    <packaging>jar</packaging>\n    10→\n    11→    <properties>\n    12→        <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>\n    13→        <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>\n    14→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    15→        <quarkus.platform.version>3.17.8</quarkus.platform.version>\n    16→        <compiler-plugin.version>3.13.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    17→        <surefire-plugin.version>3.5.3</surefire-plugin.version>\n    18→        <lombok.version>1.18.38</lombok.version>\n    19→    </properties>\n    20→\n    21→    <dependencyManagement>\n    22→        <dependencies>\n    23→            <dependency>\n    24→                <groupId>io.quarkus.platform</groupId>\n    25→                <artifactId>quarkus-bom</artifactId>\n    26→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n    27→                <type>pom</type>\n    28→                <scope>import</scope>\n    29→            </dependency>\n    30→        </dependencies>\n    31→    </dependencyManagement>\n    32→\n    33→    <dependencies>\n    34→        <!-- Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive with Jackson -->\n    35→        <dependency>\n    36→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    37→            <artifactId>quarkus-rest-jackson</artifactId>\n    38→        </dependency>\n    39→\n    40→        <!-- Quarkus Hibernate ORM (JPA) -->\n    41→        <dependency>\n    42→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    43→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-orm</artifactId>\n    44→        </dependency>\n    45→\n    46→        <!-- Quarkus JDBC PostgreSQL -->\n    47→        <dependency>\n    48→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    49→            <artifactId>quarkus-jdbc-postgresql</artifactId>\n    50→        </dependency>\n    51→\n    52→        <!-- Quarkus Bean Validation -->\n    53→        <dependency>\n    54→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    55→            <artifactId>quarkus-hibernate-validator</artifactId>\n    56→        </dependency>\n    57→\n    58→        <!-- Quarkus CDI (Arc) -->\n    59→        <dependency>\n    60→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    61→            <artifactId>quarkus-arc</artifactId>\n    62→        </dependency>\n    63→\n    64→        <!-- Quarkus Health -->\n    65→        <dependency>\n    66→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n    67→            <artifactId>quarkus-smallrye-health</artifactId>\n    68→        </dependency>\n    69→\n    70→        <!-- JWT Auth0 library (custom JWT handling) -->\n    71→        <dependency>\n    72→            <groupId>com.auth0</groupId>\n    73→            <artifactId>java-jwt</artifactId>\n    74→            <version>4.5.0</version>\n    75→        </dependency>\n    76→\n    77→        <!-- BCrypt -->\n    78→        <dependency>\n    79→            <groupId>at.favre.lib</groupId>\n    80→            <artifactId>bcrypt</artifactId>\n    81→            <version>0.10.2</version>\n    82→        </dependency>\n    83→\n    84→        <!-- Slugify -->\n    85→        <dependency>\n    86→            <groupId>com.github.slugify</groupId>\n    87→            <artifactId>slugify</artifactId>\n    88→            <version>3.0.7</version>\n    89→        </dependency>\n    90→\n    91→        <!-- Apache Commons Lang -->\n    92→        <dependency>\n    93→            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n    94→            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n    95→        </dependency>\n    96→\n    97→        <!-- Lombok -->\n    98→        <dependency>\n    99→            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n   100→            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n   101→            <version>${lombok.version}</version>\n   102→            <scope>provided</scope>\n   103→        </dependency>\n   104→\n   105→        <!-- Test dependencies -->\n   106→        <dependency>\n   107→            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n   108→            <artifactId>quarkus-junit5</artifactId>\n   109→            <scope>test</scope>\n   110→        </dependency>\n   111→        <dependency>\n   112→            <groupId>io.rest-assured</groupId>\n   113→            <artifactId>rest-assured</artifactId>\n   114→            <scope>test</scope>\n   115→        </dependency>\n   116→    </dependencies>\n   117→\n   118→    <build>\n   119→        <finalName>${project.artifactId}</finalName>\n   120→        <plugins>\n   121→            <plugin>\n   122→                <groupId>io.quarkus.platform</groupId>\n   123→                <artifactId>quarkus-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n   124→                <version>${quarkus.platform.version}</version>\n   125→                <extensions>true</extensions>\n   126→                <executions>\n   127→                    <execution>\n   128→                        <goals>\n   129→                            <goal>build</goal>\n   130→                            <goal>generate-code</goal>\n   131→                            <goal>generate-code-tests</goal>\n   132→                        </goals>\n   133→                    </execution>\n   134→                </executions>\n   135→            </plugin>\n   136→            <plugin>\n   137→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n   138→                <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n   139→                <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n   140→                <configuration>\n   141→                    <source>21</source>\n   142→                    <target>21</target>\n   143→                    <parameters>true</parameters>\n   144→                    <annotationProcessorPaths>\n   145→                        <path>\n   146→                            <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>\n   147→                            <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>\n   148→                            <version>${lombok.version}</version>\n   149→                        </path>\n   150→                    </annotationProcessorPaths>\n   151→                </configuration>\n   152→            </plugin>\n   153→            <plugin>\n   154→                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n   155→                <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>\n   156→                <version>${surefire-plugin.version}</version>\n   157→                <configuration>\n   158→                    <systemPropertyVariables>\n   159→                        <java.util.logging.manager>org.jboss.logmanager.LogManager</java.util.logging.manager>\n   160→                    </systemPropertyVariables>\n   161→                </configuration>\n   162→            </plugin>\n   163→        </plugins>\n   164→    </build>\n   165→</project>\n   166→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"41b32158-b936-4d70-a6e3-751481731df2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01736BeoaJaETmnRK6GSJfLy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see a critical problem! The project uses `quarkus-rest-jackson` (Quarkus REST / RESTEasy Reactive), but the code uses `@ApplicationPath(\"api\")` with `jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application`. \n\n**Key insight**: With `quarkus-rest-jackson` (RESTEasy Reactive), the `@ApplicationPath` annotation is honored BUT the issue is that Quarkus REST Reactive handles Jackson deserialization differently from RESTEasy Classic. In Quarkus REST Reactive, the framework uses its own serialization layer that directly uses the CDI ObjectMapper bean.\n\nThe real problem is likely that the `@Named(\"wrappingObjectMapper\")` bean is being selected by Quarkus REST as its primary ObjectMapper because it's the only `@Produces ObjectMapper` bean with `@Singleton` scope (without considering the `@Named` qualifier). Quarkus REST Reactive might not respect the `@Named` qualifier and just pick up any `ObjectMapper` bean.\n\nLet me now implement the fix. The strategy is:\n\n1. **Don't produce any ObjectMapper CDI beans** that could conflict with Quarkus's built-in one\n2. Instead, use manual instantiation in `SerializerConfig` for the wrapping and non-wrapping ObjectMappers\n3. OR switch from `quarkus-rest-jackson` to `quarkus-resteasy-jackson` (RESTEasy Classic) which works better with the existing JAX-RS code patterns\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to switch to RESTEasy Classic (`quarkus-resteasy-jackson`) since the codebase uses traditional JAX-RS patterns with `@Context`, `@NameBinding`, etc. RESTEasy Reactive has compatibility issues with some of these patterns. Let me make this change:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3272,"cache_read_input_tokens":54173,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3272,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":676},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"6e64abac-a201-4af7-8ea1-5f476dc1fb8b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01736BeoaJaETmnRK6GSJfLy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01C8YzBdkTVi5BLbEdjv759s","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__realworld__jakarta__quarkus/run_3/output/pom.xml","old_string":"        <!-- Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive with Jackson -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-rest-jackson</artifactId>\n        </dependency>","new_string":"        <!-- Quarkus RESTEasy Classic with Jackson -->\n        <dependency>\n            <groupId>io.quarkus</groupId>\n            <artifactId>quarkus-resteasy-jackson</artifactId>\n        </dependency>"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3272,"cache_read_input_tokens":54173,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3272,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":676},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"dbbba624-4cf9-42c2-a391-e256ad322c76"}
