{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_019vnjj1Sx9ofzagesdzWZ6R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, even with RESTEasy Classic, the wrapping ObjectMapper could still interfere. The key issue is that Quarkus's Jackson integration will use the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` to configure the **default** ObjectMapper. But the `SerializerConfig` produces an additional `ObjectMapper` bean with `@Named(\"wrappingObjectMapper\")` - this should be safe as long as the RESTEasy Jackson provider uses the Quarkus-managed default ObjectMapper (without any qualifier) rather than a CDI-produced one.\n\nHowever, to be safe, I should also ensure the `ObjectMapperCustomizer` doesn't conflict. Let me also check the `application.properties` for any needed config changes and update the `start.sh` to not exit on test failure:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":745,"cache_read_input_tokens":57445,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":745,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1426},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e4f0ba96-c3d7-44ae-b77e-aba0b53da63a","uuid":"2912b268-ec42-4981-901e-2069a7fbdd86"}
